  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your <strong>aubergine[s] </strong>and slice, lengthways into approx. 1cm thick slices</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688117263925-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688117263925-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688117263925-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688117263925-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688117263925-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>aubergine slices</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!), then drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: Try to spread the aubergine slices out as much as you can!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until the aubergine is tender</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the oven and set aside to cool</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688117267828-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688117267828-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688117267828-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688117267828-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688117267828-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Combine <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> (save the rest for later!) with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688117271148-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688117271148-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688117271148-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688117271148-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688117271148-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>walnuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688117274940-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688117274940-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688117274940-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688117274940-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688117274940-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> toasted walnuts</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> (reserve the pan!) and grind until very fine</p><p>Tip: No food processor? Bash the walnuts in a pestle & mortar until very fine!</p><p>Combine the <strong>ground walnuts</strong> and <strong>ground paprika </strong>in a small bowl with your <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and 2 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[5 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>– this is your <strong>walnut filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688117278932-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688117278932-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688117278932-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688117278932-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688117278932-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining diced shallot</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) <strong>ground coriander</strong> and<strong> bulgur wheat</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 15 min or until tender – this is your<strong> spicy bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688117281943-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688117281943-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688117281943-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688117281943-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1688117281943-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine slices are cool enough to handle, spread the <strong>walnut filling</strong> on each slice, then roll up the aubergine so the filling is encased – these are your <strong>Georgian-style aubergine rolls</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and most of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save some for garnish!) in a small bowl with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your<strong> coriander mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1688117285225-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1688117285225-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1688117285225-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1688117285225-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1688117285225-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Georgian-style aubergine rolls</strong> over the <strong>spicy bulgur</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>quick-pickled shallot </strong>and the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>pomegranate molasses </strong>and <strong>coriander mayo</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
